# Dashboard files and R2 before deploy

## Mandatory step

**Any change to a file under `dashboard/` that is served from R2 must be followed by an R2 upload of that file before deploying the worker.** Otherwise the live site will serve stale dashboard pages.

## When this applies

- You edited or added any file under `dashboard/` (e.g. `dashboard/cloud.html`, `dashboard/agent.html`, `dashboard/chats.html`, etc.).
- You are about to run `npm run deploy` or `./scripts/deploy-with-record.sh`.

## What to do

1. **Before running deploy**, for each changed file under `dashboard/` that is served from R2 (HTML and any other static assets that live at `static/dashboard/`):
   - Upload it to bucket **agent-sam** at key **static/dashboard/<filename>**.
2. **Command** (from repo root). **Always include `--remote`** — without it, uploads go to local R2 only and production is unchanged:

   ```bash
   ./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object put agent-sam/static/dashboard/<filename> --file=dashboard/<filename> --content-type=text/html --remote -c wrangler.production.toml
   ```

   For example, after changing `dashboard/cloud.html`:

   ```bash
   ./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object put agent-sam/static/dashboard/cloud.html --file=dashboard/cloud.html --content-type=text/html --remote -c wrangler.production.toml
   ```

3. **Then** run deploy.

Do not deploy the worker until the relevant dashboard file(s) have been uploaded to R2. This keeps every page you touch in sync with production.
